com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution

Class SPRPrimitive

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.kuka.roboticsAPI.controllerModel.sunrise.execution.SPRPrimitive
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    MotionSprPrimitive

    public class SPRPrimitive
extends Object
    A primitive consisting of exactly one SPR that has the same life cycle as the Primitive. Note: While it is allowed to use this class for Motion SPRs, consider using MotionSprPrimitive instead, in order to be able to handle the stop/pause events.
    This element is an undocumented internal feature. It is not intended to be used by applications as it might change or be removed in future versions.

        protected final void setState(ExecutionState newState,

      • stateFromSpr

        protected com.kuka.util.Pair<ExecutionState,String> stateFromSpr(SPRRuntime sprRuntime,
                                                                 SPRState newState)
        Utility method: Examines the given SPR and the given state for error conditions and maps them to an ExecutionState.
        Parameters:
        sprRuntime - the SPR to examine.
        newState - The state of the SPR to consider. This is a separate parameter for this method because the state of the SPR can change asynchronously.
        Returns:
        a Pair consisting of a corresponding ExecutionState and an error string. The string can be null.
